        "name": "How long does a solar plant SCADA system modernization project take?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A full solar plant SCADA system modernization at a utility-scale site typically takes 6 to 18 months from initial audit to final commissioning closeout. Timeline depends on plant size, historian data volume, number of devices, and whether the utility requires a new interconnection test. A 50 MW plant with a clean tag database and cooperative utility can complete in 8 to 10 months."
