        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you test solar SCADA failover without taking the plant offline?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Solar SCADA failover testing should be performed during a scheduled low-generation window, typically before sunrise or during a forecast overcast period. The test procedure is: confirm both servers are synchronized, isolate the primary server network connection, verify the standby promotes to primary automatically within the defined RTO (typically under 30 seconds for hot standby), confirm all alarm and control functions are operating, then restore the primary and verify it takes back the active role without data loss. Document the test results as evidence for NERC CIP compliance and O&M records."
        }
