        "name": "What is the maximum copper Ethernet run length for a solar DAS network?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "IEEE 802.3 limits copper 100BASE-TX to 100 meters per segment. In solar DAS applications, allow no more than 80 meters; actual routed cable length through trays and conduit is typically 15–25% longer than the direct distance, and EMI exposure from nearby inverter AC cables increases proportionally with run length."
