      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why is fiber the preferred medium for utility-scale solar data acquisition system (DAS) networks?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Fiber is immune to electromagnetic interference from inverters and AC power cables, immune to ground potential differences across large sites, and has attenuation below 0.4 dB/km, making distance a non-issue for any utility-scale site. A fiber ring topology adds path redundancy: a single cable cut reroutes traffic automatically, maintaining data flow."
